FBIS4-6574 "dreas078_c_94008" FBIS-EAS-94-078 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 North Korea U.S.-ROK 19-20 Apr War Exercises Reported U.S.-ROK 19-20 Apr War Exercises Reported `Surprise Strike' Exercise SK2204053494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0423 GMT 22 Apr 94 SK2204053494 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists and the South Korean puppets on April 20 staged an air war exercise against the North simulating a surprise bombing on targets with the mobilisation of more than 300 fighter-bombers, assault planes, observation planes and reconnaissance planes after creating an electronic jamming in the skies above Chungju, Yongwol, Wonju, Kanghwa Island, Pochon and Yonchon of South Korea, according to military sources. This exercise staged under the command of an E-3 early warning plane was a very dangerous war gamble aimed at a surprise strike at the northern half of Korea. This vividly shows that the U.S. imperialists are racing headlong along the road of confrontation and war on the Korean peninsula.
